The paper deals with optimization problems in the context of Gaussian MIMO broadcast channels, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses beamforming optimization, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI) and multiple-input multiple-output systems (cs.MM). The paper uses Lagrange duality, which is a technique commonly used in optimization and machine learning (cs.LG).
